FBIS4-1474 "drafr083_c_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-083 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Police Raid Right-Wing Arms Caches in Pretoria Police Raid Right-Wing Arms Caches in Pretoria MB2904065894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 29 Apr 94 MB2904065894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The police have raided three right-wing weapons caches near Pretoria and Brits. Newspaper reports say the weapons were found on farms near Brits and in Lynnwood, Pretoria. The latest finds follow the arrests of 32 people in connection with alleged right-wing terror attacks. Members of the AWB [Afrikaner Resistance Movement] Ystergarde [Iron Guard] are among the suspects.
